Questions:
Find the moment of inertia of a triangle of base a and height h with respect to:
(1) the base;
(2) a straight line parallel to the base through the vertex;
(3) a straight line parallel to the base through the centre of gravity of the triangle.

Find the particular value of the function:
(1) z = [arc tan(x+y)/arc tan(x-y)]² for x = (1+√3)/2, y = (1-√3)/2;
(2) z = e^(sin(x+y)) for x = y = π/2;
(3) z = y^(x²-1) + x^(y²-1) for x = 2, y = 2; x = 1, y = 2; x = 2, y = 1.

Answers:
With 0 ≤ x ≤ 1, 0 ≤ y ≤ 1 S = xy; 
with 0 ≤ x ≤ 1, 1 ≤ y S = x; 
with 1 ≤ x, 0 ≤ y ≤ 1 S = y; 
with 1 ≤ x ≤ 2; 1 ≤ y ≤ 2 S = xy — x — y + 2; 
with 1 ≤ x ≤ 2; 2 ≤ y S = x; 
with 2 ≤ x, 1 ≤ y ≤ 2 S = y; 
with 2 ≤ x, 2 ≤ y S = 2. 
The function is not defined for x < 0 and y < 0.
